more widespread cousin, the white-collared swift. Weight in the species can vary from 115 to 225 g (4.1 to 7.9 oz) with a reported average weight of 175 g (6.2 oz). The adults are brown-black, glossed blue on the back, and have a white crescent on the nape. The tail is fairly squared off, but can be held in a minorly notched way when flying. The more widespread white-collared swift is similar, sometimes measuring nearly as large. The white-collar, however, has a complete white collar (whereas the White-nape has no white on the underside) and has a strongly notched tail. This is a gregarious species, with breeding colonies sometimes including up to 200 individuals. It has been observed roosting alongside several other species of swift as well. Breeding colonies often forage together to several miles away from the breeding site. It has a powerful, fast and direct flight, and will ascent thermals to great heights. White-naped swifts feeds in flight on a variety of flying insects, including beetles, bees and flying ants. The nest is typically a shallow depression (made by the parents) in dry sand, usually lacking any materials or saliva, although they are apparently picky about the consistency of the soil used. The nests have usually been found in caves, with the nest located on ledges off the main chamber. Two white eggs are laid. The details of brooding behavior are not known. This swift is normally silent when seen solitary and noisy when encountered in a group. The call is described as cree-cree-cree. The call is delivered both while in flight and while perched on the walls of the nesting cave. References Chantler and Driessens, Swifts ISBN 1-873403-83-6", "shortSummary": "The white-naped swift (Streptoprocne semicollaris) is the largest representative of the swift family in the New World and one of the two la…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b3/ChaeturaSemicollarisSmit.jpg/960px-ChaeturaSemicollarisSmit.jpg", "order": "Apodiformes", "family": "Apodidae", "genus": "Streptoprocne", "species": "Streptoprocne semicollaris", "orderCn": "雨燕目", "familyCn": "雨燕科", "genusCn": "白領黑雨燕屬", "speciesCn": "白枕黑雨燕", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-apodiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-apodidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-streptoprocne", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-streptoprocne-semicollaris", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-apodiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-apodidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-streptoprocne", "species": "taxonomy-species-streptoprocne-semicollaris"}, "expandable": true, "x": -58.42, "y": 893.52, "z": -11.37}], "links": [{"key": "bird-white-naped-swift-b927dd4f__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-streptoprocne-semicollaris", "source": "bird-white-naped-swift-b927dd4f", "target": "taxonomy-species-streptoprocne-semicollaris", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-streptoprocne-semicollaris__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-streptoprocne", "source": "taxonomy-species-streptoprocne-semicollaris", "target": "taxonomy-genus-streptoprocne", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：白枕黑雨燕 属于属 白領黑雨燕屬。"}]}
